				<div class="titBullet"></div>
				<h1><a href="linux-tutorial-blog-is-no-longer-frozen">Linux Tutorial Blog is no longer frozen!</a></h1>
				<div class="metaRight">
				<img src="../wp-content/themes/colorbold/images/ico_user.png" alt="Author" /> <a href="2007/01" title="Visit rechosen&#8217;s website" rel="external">rechosen</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="../wp-content/themes/colorbold/images/ico_folder.png" alt="Category" /> <a href="../category/news" title="View all posts in News" rel="category tag">News</a>	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="../wp-content/themes/colorbold/images/ico_tag.png" alt="Tags" />  <a href="http://www.linuxtutorialblog.com/tag/frozen" rel="nofollow tag">frozen</a></div>
				<p>Whether this was caused by global warming or by the many visitors that kept on coming during the time Linux Tutorial Blog was frozen we'll never know, but this blog is melting. Featuring a new tutorial and some upcoming changes, LTB is once more a place to keep watching, a "regular Linux tutorial source". I hope you will enjoy this new breeze of activity!<span id="more-104"></span></p>
<p>The upcoming changes are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Revenue of this site will now be invested into my study. It's an expensive thing to attend a university for quite some upcoming years!</li>
<li>I will overlook the existing tutorials for language errors and places where they should be updated/expanded. You can especially expect a major overhaul of the flac to mp3 solution.</li>
<li>The text links area on the left will get a new purpose.</li>
<li>I may experiment with new advertising types. Whatever I do, I will try to keep it sufficiently non-obtrusive.</li>
<li>You may have already seem them: the site now features "Related Posts" under each post.</li>
</ul>
<p>Well then, I'd love to hear something from you! Got suggestions for more changes? Are you happy the blog is active again? Anything else to say? Feel more than free to comment!</p>
<p>Rechosen</p>
 
